<h1>Latest news 08-04-2023</h1>


 <h2>NuTyX 23.05.0 available with cards 2.6.7</h2>
  <p>
   Spiky and me are happy to announce the new version of NuTyX 23.05.0 and cards 2.6.7 .
  <p>
   New toolchain gcc 13.1.0, glibc 2.37 and binutils 2.40 .
  <p>
   SysV in 3.06 and systemd in 253.0 .
  <p>
   The xorg-server graphics server version 21.1.8,
   the Mesa 3D library in 23.0.3, Gtk4 4.10.3
   and Qt 6.5.0.
  <p>
   The nvidia driver is update to version  530.41.03 .
   The legacy driver 470.xx series in version 470.182.03 .
   The legacy driver 390.xx series in version 390.157 .
  <p>
   The python interpreter is updated to version 3.11.3.
  <p>
   The XFCE desktop environment is updated to version 4.18.3.
  <p>
   The MATE desktop environment is a 1.26.1 version .
  <p>
   The GNOME desktop environment is also updated to version 44.0
   <p>
   The KDE desktop environment is available in Plasma 5.27.4, Framework 5.105.0
   and applications in 23.04.0.
  <p>
   Available browsers are: Firefox 112.0.2, Chromium 113.0.5672.63, Epiphany 44.2, etc
  <p>
   Many desktop applications have been updated as well like Telegram-desktop 4.8.1,
   Thunderbird 102.10.1, Scribus 1.5.8, Libreoffice 7.5.3.2, Gimp 2.10.34, etc.
  <p>
   Core NuTyX ships with Long Term Support (LTS) kernels:
   4.14.314, 4.19.282, 5.4.242, 5.10.179, 5.15.109, 6.1.26
   and the latest stable version 6.3.1 .
  <p>
   The kernel change logs are available here:
  <p>
  <a href="https://cdn.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v4.x/ChangeLog-4.14.314">kernel 4.14.314 changelog</a>
  <p>
   <a href="https://cdn.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v4.x/ChangeLog-4.19.282">kernel 4.19.282 changelog</a>
  <p>
   <a href="https://cdn.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v5.x/ChangeLog-5.4.242">kernel 5.4.242 changelog</a>
  <p>
   <a href="https://cdn.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v5.x/ChangeLog-5.10.179">kernel 5.10.179 changelog</a>
  <p>
   <a href="https://cdn.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v5.x/ChangeLog-5.15.109">kernel 5.15.109 changelog</a>
  <p>
   <a href="https://cdn.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v6.x/ChangeLog-6.1.26">kernel 6.1.26 changelog</a>
  <p>
   <a href="https://cdn.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v6.x/ChangeLog-6.3.1">kernel 6.3.1 changelog</a>
  <p>
   A BASE ISO (proposed in command line interface edition only without graphical interface).
  <p>
   13 desktops are now available in:
   XORG,
   OPENBOX,
   LXDE,
   XFCE4,
   JWM,
   CDE,
   LXQT,
   ENLIGHTENMENT,
   MATE,
   CINNAMON,
   BUDGIE,
   GNOME,
   KDE5.
  <p>
   They are available on the <a href="downloads">download page.</a>

 <h2>Bugs fixes</h2>
  <p>
   Impossible to use any other file system then ext3/4 at installation time.
   The initrd doesn't detect the choosen file system.
  <p>
   If an ISO is created with the 4.14.x kernel, it won't start.
  <p>
   The nautilus file manager requires the gtk4 library as a dependency, it is not installed automatically.

 <h2>Upgrade process</h2>
  <p>
   A simple:
 </p><pre class="command_user"><kbd>sudo cards upgrade</kbd></pre>
   will make it.
   
 <h2>Thanks</h2>
